It is highly nutritious, environmentally friendly, can be farmed efficiently, and can serve as a means of livelihood in impoverished areas. Scientific research is progressing steadily, mainly in the Netherlands, and the edible insect business is accelerating in various countries such as France and the United States. This book has attracted worldwide attention and is being published in the hope that children, who will be responsible for the future, will understand the idea of ​​eating insects as a solution to future food problems. ■Synopsis■ Mai-Mai, a mysterious girl who suddenly transferred to her school, brings bugs for her lunch and begins eating them, and she also recommends them to her classmates. She wants everyone to know about eating insects, so Mai-Mai and her classmate Osamu participate in the ``World Insect Eating Festival'' sponsored by the United Nations to show off the wonders of eating insects to the whole world, but..."},"links":{"amz":"https://www.amazon.co.jp/新世紀食糧記-ムシグルメン-マイマイの人類虫食計画-飲茶-ebook/dp/B07SSWVNVR","ebj":"https://ebookjapan.yahoo.co.jp/books/546521/"},"originalLanguage":"ja","publicationDemographic":"shounen","contentRating":"safe","tags":[{"id":"e5301a23-ebd9-49dd-a0cb-2add944c7fe9","name":{"en":"Slice of Life"}},{"id":"ea2bc92d-1c26-4930-9b7c-d5c0dc1b6869","name":{"en":"Cooking"}},{"id":"f5ba408b-0e7a-484d-8d49-4e9125ac96de","name":{"en":"Full Color"}}]}

2119894f-f5ca-45b2-9270-855052b1ed61:::||@!@||:::2024-02-20T00:47:56:::||@!@||:::{"id":"2119894f-f5ca-45b2-9270-855052b1ed61","title":{"en":"Dark Hunter: Tsukumo Ranzou"},"altTitles":[{"ja-ro":"Yamigarishi: Tsukumo Ranzou"},{"ja":"九十九乱蔵 闇狩り師"},{"ja-ro":"Tsukumo Ranzou: Yamigarishi"},{"ja":"闇狩り師 九十九乱蔵"},{"ja-ro":"Tsukumo Ranzou"}],"lastChapter":"4","description":{"en":"\"Yamihunshi'' is one of Baku Yumemakura's masterpieces. The condition for making it into a comic was \"if Ken Ishikawa could draw it.'' “I am a fan of Mr. Ishikawa's drawings and stories, and there is something particularly irresistible about the frighteningness when he depicts mechanics that look like living internal organs.” (“About the Dark Hunter”) (From the 19th Ranzo). As those words suggest, Ken Ishikawa's unique writing style skillfully depicts the activities of Kujuku Ranzo, whose business is to banish demons, with a touch of humor at times. Kujuku Ranzo, a \"tatarare-ya\" who is known as Mr. Sennin and has mastered Chinese martial arts, is visiting a villa to ward off evil spirits at the request of Zennosuke Tamba. 28839c58-a8aa-4bc5-bb0a-1f585288a300:::||@!@||:::2024-02-20T00:48:08:::||@!@||:::{"id":"28839c58-a8aa-4bc5-bb0a-1f585288a300","title":{"en":"The Phantom Thief Baron Bat"},"altTitles":[{"ja-ro":"Koumori Danshaku"},{"ja":"こうもり男爵"},{"ja-ro":"Kaitou Koumori Otoko"},{"ja":"怪盗こうもり男爵"},{"ja-ro":"Kaitou Koumori Danshaku"}],"lastChapter":"22","description":{"en":"London at the beginning of the 20th century. What is the true identity of the mysterious man ``Baron Phantom Thief Bat'' who helps the weak and frustrates the strong? Sachiko Asuka's masterpiece, that romantic and stylish suspense comedy, is finally back! ! Don't miss this masterpiece girls' manga from the Showa era following \"Yukiko Tani\"!\n\nSachiko Asuka's \"The Phantom Thief Bat Baron\" first appeared in Kodansha's \"Weekly Shojo Friend\" in 1967, then Shueisha's \"Weekly Seventeen\" in 1969, Shogakukan's \"Weekly Shojo Comic\" in 1973, and other weekly magazines from three companies. This is a popular suspense comedy series released in. Set in post-World War I London, the story was very popular at the time of its release, depicting a number of incidents surrounding an unknown robber named Baron Bat. In contrast to the stylishness of Baron Bat, who appears with a fluttering black cloak, Professor Isaac Asimov is a versatile genius scientist but a bit clumsy (we implicitly understand that he is Baron Bat!), and a beautiful woman. It features attractive characters such as the strong-willed newspaper reporter Betty, and the story is full of suspense, action, romance, a bit of slapstick, serious scenes with occasional dark shadows of history, and plenty of parody.\nThis fantastic series, which has been difficult to read for many years, has now been compiled into one volume for the first time. In addition, it includes valuable unreleased episodes and two spin-off short stories. This is truly a \"definitive edition!\" that fans of the past cannot miss no matter what.\n\nIn addition, three unique short stories from outside the series are also included. (\"The Strange Story of Elsinore Castle,\" \"Monsieur Monsieur's Great Strategy,\" and \"The Beautiful Vampire\") Even those who come into contact with Sachiko Asuka's works for the first time can enjoy her diverse charm.\nOf course, this is a fulfilling book that also includes an interview with Sachiko Asuka and a list of her works.\n\nSpecial contribution by manga artist Yasuko Sakata. Drawn under the name Fujio Ashizuka, he moved from Toyama to Tokyo and brought it to several publishers, but it was not accepted, and after being introduced by Osamu Tezuka, the company decided to make it into a book. However, because the cover was written by Noboru Oshiro and was published in conjunction with other manga artists' works, the two subsequent reprints had Fujiko draw a new cover and the coupling work was removed, leaving the book as original. It wasn't. This time, we have achieved a complete reprint that faithfully reproduces the text in two colors based on the original that Leiji Matsumoto had preserved.\nEarth was frozen by the ice bomb used by the S Federation during World War III. What the boy, who was confined in a shelter and revived 100 years later, sees is an Earth that has recovered from the damage caused by the ice bomb and has been rebuilt as a utopia with advanced scientific civilization.
